data.title: Index To Analecta Hibernicae
data.meta_description: Index to Analecta Hibernicae - Free download as PDF File (.pdf), Text File (.txt) or read online for free. Ferdinando d'Adda was a Papal nuncio (representative) in England from 1685-1688. He exchanged letters with Cardinal Cibo regarding his duties, which included urging assistance for poor Catholics in 1687 and consecrating a new Irish bishop in 1688. D'Adda also discussed Irish episcopal arrangements with Lord Sunderland and informed some Irish prelates of dispensations regarding degrees of affinity.
